Description:
On the beach of a small island, you see an old man with a small flock of parrots. As you approach him, he says:

“Ahoy, friends. As you can see, I am in good company, and you too could be if you buy one of these beauties from me. This has been a good year, and I can sell you a young one for just 400g. Think about it! After all, no sailor worth his title sails without a trusty parrot companion!”

The parrots laugh at once when the man waves at them, but it is clear that some of them are better trained than others.
DescriptionAction: Do you want to buy a parrot?
